A complex river system viewed from above in Studio Ghibli animation style, where a single clear turquoise stream enters from one side and gradually branches into an intricate delta of countless smaller waterways, some flowing through dense bamboo forests, others winding around moss-covered stones and tiny islands with miniature pagodas. The water transitions from simple and calm at the source to increasingly elaborate channels that weave and reconnect in organic patterns. Soft afternoon sunlight filters through scattered clouds, casting gentle golden reflections on the water surfaces. Small colorful fish can be seen swimming through the clearer sections. The landscape features the characteristic Ghibli palette of lush greens, warm earth tones, and dreamy atmospheric haze in the distance where the countless streams eventually merge back into a single peaceful outlet.
